OL,3,CLabour to drop #28 billion-a-year
OL,4,Cgreen spending pledge
OL,6,FLast year, Labour adjusted its
OL,7,Foriginal plan by saying the #28
OL,8,Fbillion-a-year spending target would
OL,9,Flikely be met in the second half of a
OL,10,Ffirst parliament, rather than
OL,11,Fimmediately, if the party wins the
OL,12,Fnext election.
OL,14,FThe party has since insisted the
OL,15,Fpledge is subject to its fiscal rules,
OL,16,Fwhich include getting debt falling as
OL,17,Fa percentage of GDP, as it seeks to
OL,18,Freassure voters it would handle the
OL,19,Feconomy responsibly in government.
