OL,6,FChief Secretary to the Treasury Laura
OL,7,FTrott said: "This is a serious moment
OL,8,Fwhich confirms Labour have no plan for
OL,9,Fthe UK, creating uncertainty for
OL,10,Fbusiness and our economy. On the day
OL,11,Fthat Labour are finalising their
OL,12,Fmanifesto, Keir Starmer is torpedoing
OL,13,Fwhat he has claimed to be his central
OL,14,Feconomic policy purely for short-term
OL,15,Fcampaigning reasons.
OL,17,F"He must explain how he can keep the
OL,18,F#28 billion spending when he is
OL,19,Ffinally admitting he doesn't have a
OL,20,Fplan to pay for it.
